ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you've taken Physiology and are looking to augment your knowledge, this is a good course for you - it doesn't require a lot of time outside of class, and is generally engaging and interesting during class itself.
You learn a variety of topics, but the teaching style of the professors vary a lot. Lectures by Dr. Boulpaep are very fast paced while lectures from Dr. Sigworth are math oriented. I
C&MP 560 explores the role of molecular machines, which includes ion channels, transporters, and motor proteins, in human physiology.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course doesn't directly apply to my research, but was a nice augmentation to the topics I learned in Physiology
I don't think this course is too relevant to my research because the course is highly focused on membrane channels and disease that originate from them.
This course has given me basic knowledge about the function of ion channels and other transport proteins that will be useful throughout my scientific career.
